Title: In a Manner I Won't Forget
---
Tell me, love, what I need right now so that I might sing, and be alive,
 as my every cell craves.
Tell me, dear, what I need right now, but in a manner I won't soon forget.
Then the world began to sway, its hips invited my arms, its feet placed mine
 upon them, that made all my effort easy.
A father's toes lifting a child's in dance caused God to pull out a drum.
The Beloved belted out a tune, that went, "Nothing to follow ... for I
 will move you. You need not do a damn thing ... just laugh."
